@## Inline, Internal, External:-

1. Inline(In .html file):
<body>
  <tag style=".......;"></tag>
</body>

2. Internal(In .html file):
<head>
  <style>
    .......;
  </style>
</head>

3. External(In .css file):
........;

______________________________________________________________________
#. Text & Font Properties-

color –> Defines the foreground color of text inside an element.
font-size –> Specifies the size of the text using units like px, em, rem, or %.
font-family –> Sets the typeface of the text, including fallback fonts.
font-weight –> Controls the thickness of text (normal, bold, 100–900).
font-style –> Applies italic or normal styling to text.
text-align –> Aligns inline content horizontally within its container.
text-decoration –> Adds decorative lines such as underline or line-through.
text-transform –> Changes text case (uppercase, lowercase, capitalize).
letter-spacing –> Adjusts spacing between individual characters.
line-height –> Controls vertical spacing between lines of text.

______________________________________________________________________
#. Box Model Properties-

width –> Sets the horizontal size of an element’s content area.
height –> Sets the vertical size of an element’s content area.
max-width –> Limits the maximum width an element can grow to.
min-width –> Ensures the element does not shrink below a certain width.
margin –> Adds space outside the element, separating it from others.
margin-top/right/bottom/left –> Controls margin on individual sides.
padding –> Adds space inside the element between content and border.
padding-top/right/bottom/left –> Controls padding on individual sides.
border –> Adds a border around the element combining width, style, and color.
border-width –> Defines the thickness of the border.
border-style –> Specifies border pattern (solid, dotted, dashed, etc.).
border-color –> Sets the color of the border.
border-radius –> Rounds the corners of an element’s border.
box-sizing –> Determines whether padding and border are included in width/height calculations.

______________________________________________________________________
#. Background Properties-

background-color –> Sets the background color of an element.
background-image –> Applies an image as the background of an element.
background-size –> Controls scaling of the background image (cover, contain).
background-position –> Defines where the background image is placed.
background-repeat –> Controls whether the background image repeats or not.

______________________________________________________________________
#. Layout & Positioning-

display –> Defines how an element is rendered (block, inline, flex, grid, etc.).
position –> Specifies positioning method (static, relative, absolute, fixed, sticky).
top –> Moves a positioned element downward from its reference point.
bottom –> Moves a positioned element upward from the bottom reference.
left –> Moves a positioned element rightward from the left reference.
right –> Moves a positioned element leftward from the right reference.
overflow –> Controls what happens when content exceeds container size.
visibility –> Hides an element while keeping its layout space reserved.

______________________________________________________________________
#. Flexbox Properties(Very Important)-

justify-content –> Aligns flex items horizontally within a flex container.
align-items –> Aligns flex items vertically within a flex container.
flex-direction –> Sets direction of flex items (row, column).
flex-wrap –> Allows flex items to wrap onto multiple lines.
gap –> Defines spacing between flex or grid items.

______________________________________________________________________
#. Grid Properties-

grid-template-columns –> Defines number and size of grid columns.
grid-template-rows –> Defines number and size of grid rows.
grid-gap / gap –> Sets spacing between grid rows and columns.

______________________________________________________________________
#. Effects & Advanced Properties-

opacity –> Controls transparency level of an element (0–1).
box-shadow –> Adds shadow effect around an element’s box.
text-shadow –> Adds shadow effect to text characters.
transform –> Applies visual transformations like rotate, scale, translate.
transition –> Adds smooth animation when CSS properties change.
z-index –> Controls stacking order of overlapping positioned elements.
cursor –> Changes mouse pointer appearance when hovering over element.
